WEBVTT

00:00:59.583 --> 00:01:02.371
I'll get straight to the point.

00:01:03.670 --> 00:01:07.340
After reviewing all the circumstances
and the submitted materials,

00:01:07.340 --> 00:01:09.370
at this time,

00:01:09.370 --> 00:01:12.248
the two of you are not considered suitable

00:01:12.248 --> 00:01:15.008
to serve as Woo Joo's guardians.

00:01:17.336 --> 00:01:19.297
What do you mean by that...

00:01:19.297 --> 00:01:20.770
Not suitable?

00:01:20.770 --> 00:01:22.314
How is that possible
when we're Woo Joo's family...

00:01:22.314 --> 00:01:23.940
At the moment,

00:01:23.940 --> 00:01:25.775
the child is probably experiencing
a very emotionally unstable period

00:01:25.775 --> 00:01:27.722
because of the parents' sudden absence.

00:01:27.722 --> 00:01:29.487
But with all the late nights at work,

00:01:29.487 --> 00:01:32.490
and with caretakers constantly changing
over the last few months,

00:01:32.490 --> 00:01:34.729
the environment around you right now

00:01:34.729 --> 00:01:37.746
doesn't seem like it can give
the child the stability he needs.

00:01:37.746 --> 00:01:40.943
And on top of that, the fact
that there's been conflict among relatives

00:01:40.943 --> 00:01:43.877
isn't something I can just ignore.

00:01:43.877 --> 00:01:45.211
Also,

00:01:45.211 --> 00:01:47.297
since I saw part of it with my own eyes,

00:01:47.297 --> 00:01:48.590
honestly,

00:01:48.590 --> 00:01:51.287
I can't really say
that the two of you are qualified

00:01:51.287 --> 00:01:53.547
to become Woo Joo's guardians.

00:01:55.138 --> 00:01:56.473
Investigator,

00:01:56.473 --> 00:01:58.489
we truly are doing everything we can.

00:01:58.489 --> 00:01:59.684
Everything you mentioned,

00:01:59.684 --> 00:02:01.531
we'll make sure

00:02:01.531 --> 00:02:04.064
none of it ever happens again.

00:02:04.064 --> 00:02:06.191
Could you please reconsider just once?

00:02:06.191 --> 00:02:08.471
In the end, it won't be my call anyway.

00:02:08.471 --> 00:02:11.106
The court will make the final decision.

00:02:11.766 --> 00:02:13.553
That said...

00:02:14.783 --> 00:02:18.022
- Gosh.
- You're good.

00:02:18.022 --> 00:02:19.829
Hey there.

00:02:19.829 --> 00:02:21.825
You're back?

00:02:23.416 --> 00:02:24.584
Woo Joo.

00:02:24.584 --> 00:02:25.961
Did you behave and listen to the adults?

00:02:25.961 --> 00:02:26.864
Of course.

00:02:26.864 --> 00:02:28.699
I told him you guys had gone out
to handle something,

00:02:28.699 --> 00:02:30.284
and he waited so nicely like a big kid.

00:02:30.284 --> 00:02:32.092
Oh, would you like some sikhye?

00:02:32.092 --> 00:02:34.719
Ae Ja made it,
and it's not overly sweet. It's really tasty.

00:02:34.719 --> 00:02:36.631
Woo Joo, want to try some?

00:02:37.847 --> 00:02:39.474
- Want just a little, Woo Joo?
- You don't want it?

00:02:39.474 --> 00:02:40.475
- No?
- No.

00:02:40.475 --> 00:02:41.988
Then I'll drink it.

00:02:41.988 --> 00:02:44.145
I'd better get going.

00:02:44.145 --> 00:02:45.591
What's wrong?

00:02:45.591 --> 00:02:47.399
Are you sick?

00:02:47.399 --> 00:02:48.566
Oh, no.

00:02:48.566 --> 00:02:50.110
I'm just kind of worn out.

00:02:50.110 --> 00:02:52.397
And I need to clean up at home too.

00:02:53.238 --> 00:02:54.739
Okay, head in and rest.

00:02:54.739 --> 00:02:56.199
I'll bring Woo Joo in.

00:02:56.199 --> 00:02:57.895
Yeah, thanks.

00:02:57.895 --> 00:02:59.947
- I'll head in now, then.
- Okay.

00:02:59.947 --> 00:03:01.647
Go on in.

00:03:06.543 --> 00:03:08.503
Did something happen?

00:03:08.503 --> 00:03:10.964
Did something go wrong at the courthouse?

00:03:10.964 --> 00:03:12.876
Well...

00:03:14.134 --> 00:03:16.761
What? Not suitable?

00:03:16.761 --> 00:03:19.472
What kind of ridiculous talk is that?

00:03:19.472 --> 00:03:21.405
What? Maybe with someone else,

00:03:21.405 --> 00:03:23.560
but saying Hyun Jin and you
aren't fit for this?

00:03:23.560 --> 00:03:25.061
That's way too harsh.

00:03:25.061 --> 00:03:28.356
Next time, we need to prove
to them that they're wrong.

00:03:28.356 --> 00:03:31.929
No wonder Hyun Jin looked so upset.

00:03:31.929 --> 00:03:34.481
She must feel awful inside.

00:03:41.327 --> 00:03:42.746
Still,

00:03:42.746 --> 00:03:45.206
there's a chance I could be mistaken.

00:03:45.206 --> 00:03:47.576
So I'll check it myself.

00:03:47.576 --> 00:03:49.697
I'll personally go visit

00:03:49.697 --> 00:03:51.171
the house where the child is currently living

00:03:51.171 --> 00:03:52.491
and take a much closer look

00:03:52.491 --> 00:03:55.627
at everything more carefully.

00:03:58.887 --> 00:04:02.509
I still have a chance, though.

00:04:04.059 --> 00:04:06.978
I can turn things around next time.

00:04:06.978 --> 00:04:09.599
Woo Joo, believe in me.

00:04:16.072 --> 00:04:18.364
[Episode 12]

00:04:18.364 --> 00:04:20.364
Since it's for a social media campaign,

00:04:20.364 --> 00:04:22.327
bold visuals definitely work better.

00:04:22.327 --> 00:04:24.190
If everything's fine on Filmpluto's side,

00:04:24.190 --> 00:04:26.498
we were wondering
if we could move the shoot up a little.

00:04:26.498 --> 00:04:27.610
Would that be okay with you?

00:04:27.610 --> 00:04:28.917
Oh, the shoot?

00:04:28.917 --> 00:04:31.405
Well, the tteokbokki meal kit
we released this time

00:04:31.405 --> 00:04:33.797
is going absolutely crazy
on social media right now.

00:04:33.797 --> 00:04:35.576
And when things take off like that,

00:04:35.576 --> 00:04:37.161
we have to keep riding that momentum.

00:04:37.161 --> 00:04:38.384
This is perfect timing.

00:04:38.384 --> 00:04:40.095
I saw it on social media too.

00:04:40.095 --> 00:04:41.846
It seriously looks like it's fully gone viral.

00:04:41.846 --> 00:04:43.459
How does the 20th sound?

00:04:43.459 --> 00:04:45.886
That works for us.

00:04:46.684 --> 00:04:48.673
We're good that day too.

00:04:48.673 --> 00:04:51.342
We don't have any other shoots
that overlap that day, right?

00:04:51.342 --> 00:04:52.385
[Mon. the 20th, home visit by investigator]
That's a huge relief.

00:04:52.385 --> 00:04:55.429
So should we go ahead and confirm the 20th?

00:04:55.429 --> 00:04:57.397
Did you say the 20th?

00:04:59.058 --> 00:05:00.851
Then I guess there's no other option.

00:05:00.851 --> 00:05:02.311
You obviously have to go film.

00:05:02.311 --> 00:05:03.576
If that's the day of the home visit,

00:05:03.576 --> 00:05:05.411
then I need to be there too.

00:05:05.411 --> 00:05:06.440
No, it's fine.

00:05:06.440 --> 00:05:08.401
I'm using a vacation day anyway,

00:05:08.401 --> 00:05:10.208
so you don't need to be home too.

00:05:10.208 --> 00:05:11.779
So don't stress about it

00:05:11.779 --> 00:05:13.788
and just go take care of filming.

00:05:14.657 --> 00:05:16.172
I'm sorry.

00:05:16.172 --> 00:05:17.326
You don't need to be sorry.

00:05:17.326 --> 00:05:18.355
Oh, right.

00:05:18.355 --> 00:05:20.426
I'll go get Woo Joo from daycare today.

00:05:20.426 --> 00:05:22.088
Okay.

00:05:23.138 --> 00:05:26.335
But why do you seem so worn out today?

00:05:26.335 --> 00:05:28.094
No, I'm not.

00:05:40.683 --> 00:05:44.632
There, all set. You're recharged now.

00:05:44.632 --> 00:05:45.660
See?

00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:47.162
You're so pretty when you smile.

00:05:47.162 --> 00:05:48.204
You'd better get going.

00:05:48.204 --> 00:05:49.622
Seung Taek is probably waiting for you.

00:05:49.622 --> 00:05:51.291
See you at home later.

00:05:51.291 --> 00:05:52.994
I'm off.

00:05:57.922 --> 00:05:59.799
Woo Joo.

00:05:59.799 --> 00:06:03.678
Yeah. You forgot your shoes.

00:06:03.678 --> 00:06:04.864
As soon as I told him you were here,

00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:07.126
he just ran out without looking back once.

00:06:07.126 --> 00:06:09.114
Woo Joo's really crazy about you.

00:06:09.114 --> 00:06:11.030
I'll put them on him. Hand them over.

00:06:11.030 --> 00:06:12.131
Bye.

00:06:12.131 --> 00:06:14.022
- Thank you.
- Bye.

00:06:14.022 --> 00:06:15.773
Okay, let's put your shoes on.

00:06:15.773 --> 00:06:17.887
Good.

00:06:17.887 --> 00:06:20.633
Good job. Now the other one.

00:06:21.905 --> 00:06:22.989
Auntie.

00:06:22.989 --> 00:06:25.116
Yeah.

00:06:25.116 --> 00:06:27.577
Were you really that happy to see me?

00:06:27.577 --> 00:06:30.079
I didn't know you'd be this happy.

00:06:30.079 --> 00:06:31.164
Auntie.

00:06:31.164 --> 00:06:32.951
Come here.

00:06:34.626 --> 00:06:36.794
Maybe I should come get you
more often from now on.

00:06:36.794 --> 00:06:38.463
- Right?
- Yeah!

00:06:38.463 --> 00:06:40.155
Hold my hand.

00:06:40.155 --> 00:06:42.002
Let's go.

00:06:46.387 --> 00:06:47.764
Woo Joo, aren't you cold?

00:06:47.764 --> 00:06:49.015
Looks like your nose is running.

00:06:49.015 --> 00:06:51.011
Put your coat on before you go play.

00:06:51.893 --> 00:06:53.561
Are you on your way to work now?

00:06:53.561 --> 00:06:54.823
Yeah.

00:06:54.823 --> 00:06:57.739
But didn't you say
they were coming this afternoon?

00:06:57.739 --> 00:06:59.525
Why are you this busy already?

00:06:59.525 --> 00:07:00.568
The house is already spotless.

00:07:00.568 --> 00:07:02.111
It looks like there's nothing left to tidy up.

00:07:02.111 --> 00:07:04.614
I just wanted the place to feel like

00:07:04.614 --> 00:07:07.360
anyone would think it's a fine home for a kid.

00:07:08.952 --> 00:07:11.246
Are you sure you'll be all right by yourself?

00:07:11.246 --> 00:07:13.456
If I didn't have filming,
I'd be here with you myself.

00:07:13.456 --> 00:07:15.583
Don't worry about me and just get to work.

00:07:15.583 --> 00:07:16.947
I'll get back as soon as I possibly can.

00:07:16.947 --> 00:07:18.962
Make sure you call me if anything comes up.

00:07:18.962 --> 00:07:21.155
Woo Joo, I'm taking off now.

00:07:21.155 --> 00:07:22.423
Bye-bye.

00:07:22.423 --> 00:07:23.841
Right.

00:07:23.841 --> 00:07:26.636
- I'll be back.
- Okay, see you.

00:07:26.636 --> 00:07:28.506
I'm off.

00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:49.867
Even after letting the place air out,

00:07:49.867 --> 00:07:52.238
the bleach smell's still hanging around.

00:08:01.546 --> 00:08:04.159
Woo Joo.

00:08:04.159 --> 00:08:06.926
When did you take your socks off again?

00:08:06.926 --> 00:08:09.339
Let's get your socks back on.

00:08:10.430 --> 00:08:12.598
Run away.

00:08:12.598 --> 00:08:14.781
Let's run away.

00:08:14.781 --> 00:08:17.806
Keep running.

00:08:20.144 --> 00:08:22.394
It feels like you've got a fever.

00:08:24.193 --> 00:08:26.189
Please open it up.

00:08:27.433 --> 00:08:28.823
Woo Joo, come here.

00:08:28.823 --> 00:08:31.861
Stay still so I can look at your ear.

00:08:33.161 --> 00:08:35.824
This is not good.
I have to give you something for the fever.

00:08:51.864 --> 00:08:53.556
There's none left.

00:08:53.556 --> 00:08:55.336
What made you call?

00:08:55.336 --> 00:08:57.713
Oh, hello.
Woo Joo suddenly started running a fever,

00:08:57.713 --> 00:08:59.270
so I wanted to ask whether you had

00:08:59.270 --> 00:09:00.656
any fever medicine at home.

00:09:00.656 --> 00:09:02.648
I'm out right now, so what should I do?

00:09:02.648 --> 00:09:03.816
Is Woo Joo's fever pretty high?

00:09:03.816 --> 00:09:06.694
No, it's only a mild fever.

00:09:06.694 --> 00:09:08.488
He might be getting a cold.

00:09:08.488 --> 00:09:10.100
The weather's gotten cold all of a sudden,

00:09:10.100 --> 00:09:12.269
so a lot of people have been
feeling under the weather.

00:09:12.269 --> 00:09:14.531
Do you have any emergency medicine at home?

00:09:14.531 --> 00:09:16.781
Otherwise, your best bet is to take him
to the hospital.

00:09:16.781 --> 00:09:19.443
Getting to the hospital right now
is a little difficult...

00:09:19.443 --> 00:09:22.502
The court said they'd be coming by
for a home visit today, right?

00:09:22.502 --> 00:09:23.753
So what do we do now?

00:09:23.753 --> 00:09:25.030
When I headed out earlier,

00:09:25.030 --> 00:09:26.197
it seemed like Mr. Doo Sik and Ae Ja

00:09:26.197 --> 00:09:28.841
were also on their way to physical therapy.

00:09:28.841 --> 00:09:31.761
Then I'll keep checking and get back to you.

00:09:31.761 --> 00:09:33.882
Okay, thank you.

00:10:04.613 --> 00:10:06.073
Woo Joo.

00:10:06.073 --> 00:10:07.825
Woo Joo.

00:10:17.056 --> 00:10:20.268
I think getting him
to the hospital has to come first.

00:10:20.268 --> 00:10:22.931
So now the child has been hurt too?

00:10:23.729 --> 00:10:25.467
No, that's not what happened, Investigator.

00:10:25.467 --> 00:10:27.191
Neglect counts as abuse too.

00:10:27.191 --> 00:10:29.030
Being absent from a child's side

00:10:29.030 --> 00:10:30.611
when the child needs protection

00:10:30.611 --> 00:10:33.927
is neglect too, and that is clearly abuse.

00:10:35.602 --> 00:10:37.493
What are you even saying?

00:10:37.493 --> 00:10:38.522
Woo Joo.

00:10:38.522 --> 00:10:40.997
Oh my, Woo Joo. What on earth happened?

00:10:40.997 --> 00:10:42.331
What do you mean by abuse?

00:10:42.331 --> 00:10:43.541
Come on, that's too much.

00:10:43.541 --> 00:10:44.917
Abuse? Why are you saying that?

00:10:44.917 --> 00:10:46.947
I don't know exactly what went on,

00:10:46.947 --> 00:10:50.423
but you cannot just
use words like that so carelessly.

00:10:50.423 --> 00:10:53.718
Saying she neglects and abuses a baby...

00:10:53.718 --> 00:10:55.581
She's not that kind of person.

00:10:55.581 --> 00:10:57.799
I guess time will tell.

00:11:07.233 --> 00:11:09.025
Yeah. Understood.

00:11:09.025 --> 00:11:10.318
What is going on?

00:11:10.318 --> 00:11:11.527
Woo Hyun Jin?

00:11:11.527 --> 00:11:12.556
Yes?

00:11:12.556 --> 00:11:15.323
The family investigator
contacted us right away,

00:11:15.323 --> 00:11:17.533
so we came to check
on a possible child abuse case.

00:11:17.533 --> 00:11:19.160
Child abuse? I didn't do anything like that...

00:11:19.160 --> 00:11:20.745
Based on what we found at the scene

00:11:20.745 --> 00:11:22.823
and what the family investigator told us,

00:11:22.823 --> 00:11:24.531
right now, we have no choice but to believe

00:11:24.531 --> 00:11:26.446
that the child was put in harm's way.

00:11:26.446 --> 00:11:28.794
For the time being,
the child's safety has to come first,

00:11:28.794 --> 00:11:30.364
so we're placing the child
under emergency protection.

00:11:30.364 --> 00:11:33.076
What? Emergency what?
What is that even supposed to be?

00:11:33.076 --> 00:11:35.384
So what exactly are you saying you will do?

00:11:35.384 --> 00:11:37.637
By procedure, we have to separate you
from the child right away,

00:11:37.637 --> 00:11:40.709
so please cooperate with us,
even though this is abrupt.

00:11:40.709 --> 00:11:42.739
Separate us?

00:11:42.739 --> 00:11:46.507
Are you saying you're taking Woo Joo somewhere?

00:11:46.507 --> 00:11:47.674
No, no.

00:11:47.674 --> 00:11:49.364
How can you take Woo Joo away from me?

00:11:49.364 --> 00:11:52.485
Wait. I think you've got this all wrong.

00:11:52.485 --> 00:11:54.932
No, even so,

00:11:54.932 --> 00:11:57.976
how can you pull a baby away from his aunt?

00:11:57.976 --> 00:12:01.661
What did she ever do to deserve that?

00:12:01.661 --> 00:12:03.829
Emergency protection is not meant
as punishment.

00:12:03.829 --> 00:12:06.165
It's a step we're taking
to keep the child safe.

00:12:06.165 --> 00:12:07.531
When it comes to child welfare cases,

00:12:07.531 --> 00:12:09.877
the rule is to secure the child's safety first
and sort out the facts after.

00:12:09.877 --> 00:12:12.129
If our investigation finds no abuse,

00:12:12.129 --> 00:12:14.215
then every protective measure will be removed.

00:12:14.215 --> 00:12:17.405
We'd appreciate it
if you could understand and cooperate.

00:12:17.405 --> 00:12:18.511
For now,

00:12:18.511 --> 00:12:20.304
I think we should take him
to the hospital first.

00:12:20.304 --> 00:12:23.015
I'll explain everything to you.

00:12:23.015 --> 00:12:25.476
I only took my eyes off him for a moment.

00:12:25.476 --> 00:12:27.739
I can't live without Woo Joo.

00:12:27.739 --> 00:12:29.091
I'm right here,

00:12:29.091 --> 00:12:31.816
so where are you taking Woo Joo?

00:12:31.816 --> 00:12:34.763
The child's safety is our top priority,
and if you keep acting like this,

00:12:34.763 --> 00:12:36.362
it is only going to make things worse for you.

00:12:36.362 --> 00:12:37.933
All right, I've heard enough of this.

00:12:37.933 --> 00:12:39.852
And what exactly are you
going to do about it if I don't?

00:12:39.852 --> 00:12:41.645
If you keep this up,

00:12:41.645 --> 00:12:43.415
you could be booked for obstructing justice.

00:12:44.064 --> 00:12:45.489
[Child Protection Services]
Woo Joo.

00:12:45.489 --> 00:12:47.582
Woo Joo.

00:12:47.582 --> 00:12:49.827
Woo Joo.

00:12:51.916 --> 00:12:53.239
Woo Joo.

00:12:53.239 --> 00:12:57.293
I will come as fast as I can, Woo Joo.

00:13:05.766 --> 00:13:07.504
Are you sure this is not a mistake?

00:13:07.504 --> 00:13:09.214
We've been watching from up close, so we know.

00:13:09.214 --> 00:13:10.646
We know how hard Hyun Jin tried

00:13:10.646 --> 00:13:12.064
to fill a mother's role for him too.

00:13:12.064 --> 00:13:13.531
Exactly. That's what I'm saying.

00:13:13.531 --> 00:13:16.819
And besides, she only looked away for a second
to find his medicine.

00:13:16.819 --> 00:13:20.733
Then shouldn't that count
for something at least?

00:13:21.574 --> 00:13:23.864
Why is she not picking up?

00:13:23.864 --> 00:13:24.910
Tae Hyung is here.

00:13:24.910 --> 00:13:26.481
The home visit is still going on?

00:13:26.481 --> 00:13:27.858
Hey.

00:13:27.858 --> 00:13:28.873
You are only getting here now?

00:13:28.873 --> 00:13:30.666
Oh man...

00:13:30.666 --> 00:13:33.204
Well...

00:13:34.615 --> 00:13:38.536
Don't freak out, and let me explain first.

00:13:45.209 --> 00:13:47.597
[Child Protection Services]

00:14:00.141 --> 00:14:02.025
Hyun Jin.

00:14:08.072 --> 00:14:10.491
Are you all right?

00:14:13.722 --> 00:14:16.164
It's all on me.

00:14:16.781 --> 00:14:19.590
I caused all of this.

00:14:19.590 --> 00:14:22.927
If I had stayed focused on him
the whole time...

00:14:22.927 --> 00:14:23.997
No.

00:14:23.997 --> 00:14:25.405
If only I'd checked sooner

00:14:25.405 --> 00:14:28.724
so he wouldn't have come down with a cold,

00:14:28.724 --> 00:14:30.630
this never would have happened.

00:14:30.630 --> 00:14:32.019
Why would you say that?

00:14:32.019 --> 00:14:33.854
This just happened while you were trying
to find Woo Joo's medicine.

00:14:33.854 --> 00:14:37.155
- Come on, get up.
- I feel like all of this happened

00:14:37.155 --> 00:14:39.735
because I wasn't good enough,

00:14:39.735 --> 00:14:42.815
because I wasn't fit for this.

00:14:44.990 --> 00:14:47.612
I feel terrible for Woo Joo.

00:15:00.447 --> 00:15:02.591
Woo Joo, I'm sorry.

00:15:02.591 --> 00:15:05.505
He must be so scared.

00:15:15.813 --> 00:15:18.274
That startled me.

00:15:18.274 --> 00:15:21.597
You're up early.

00:15:21.597 --> 00:15:23.404
Where's Tae Hyung?

00:15:23.404 --> 00:15:25.156
I think he went out for a minute.

00:15:25.156 --> 00:15:26.198
Oh, really?

00:15:26.198 --> 00:15:28.993
Then come inside for a minute

00:15:28.993 --> 00:15:31.454
and have some fruit.

00:15:31.454 --> 00:15:35.624
Doo Sik brought back a whole basket of fruit,

00:15:35.624 --> 00:15:37.823
and we've got more than we can eat.

00:15:37.823 --> 00:15:39.044
No, really, I'm okay.

00:15:39.044 --> 00:15:40.337
Come on.

00:15:40.337 --> 00:15:42.006
Have some fruit, okay?

00:15:42.006 --> 00:15:44.085
Come on in.

00:16:05.140 --> 00:16:07.865
Eat some fruit.

00:16:07.865 --> 00:16:10.570
I'm going to step out for a bit.

00:16:11.535 --> 00:16:14.941
What's with your face?
Is it because you didn't get any sleep?

00:16:14.941 --> 00:16:15.650
Did you cry?

00:16:15.650 --> 00:16:18.153
Oh, quit talking like that and just go already.

00:16:18.153 --> 00:16:19.168
Okay.

00:16:19.168 --> 00:16:21.523
Yeah, all right.

00:16:21.523 --> 00:16:22.531
So...

00:16:22.531 --> 00:16:24.840
how long are you not allowed to see Woo Joo?

00:16:24.840 --> 00:16:25.988
Where is he now?

00:16:25.988 --> 00:16:29.720
Oh... he's staying with a foster family.

00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:30.846
- Oh, gosh.
- For now,

00:16:30.846 --> 00:16:33.823
they said the standard rule is
a 72-hour emergency separation,

00:16:33.823 --> 00:16:35.810
that's the usual procedure,

00:16:35.810 --> 00:16:38.757
and depending on what they find
in the investigation,

00:16:38.757 --> 00:16:40.397
it might be called off

00:16:40.397 --> 00:16:42.650
or it could be extended.

00:16:42.650 --> 00:16:43.905
Oh, they'll lift it.

00:16:43.905 --> 00:16:45.694
Why are you worrying so much? They'll lift it.

00:16:45.694 --> 00:16:47.488
- Go on now.
- Okay.

00:16:47.488 --> 00:16:48.823
Oh, hey.

00:16:48.823 --> 00:16:50.852
She is really good
at helping people figure things out.

00:16:50.852 --> 00:16:51.575
Tell her what's going on.

00:16:51.575 --> 00:16:53.828
- Hey, go. I said go, so get out.
- Okay.

00:16:53.828 --> 00:16:54.829
Okay, I'm leaving.

00:16:54.829 --> 00:16:56.747
I said get out.

00:16:56.747 --> 00:17:00.661
Man, maybe I should go talk
to the police chief myself.

00:17:02.211 --> 00:17:05.923
This is insanely sweet.

00:17:05.923 --> 00:17:09.337
Here, have some of this.

00:17:11.971 --> 00:17:14.139
You look like you've got no energy at all.

00:17:14.139 --> 00:17:17.386
Have you eaten?

00:17:18.811 --> 00:17:20.271
No.

00:17:20.271 --> 00:17:21.772
I haven't had any appetite.

00:17:21.772 --> 00:17:22.815
Oh, wait a second.

00:17:22.815 --> 00:17:24.400
I'll bring out some scorched rice
and gat kimchi.

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:25.776
Oh, no.

00:17:25.776 --> 00:17:27.403
I'm really fine.

00:17:27.403 --> 00:17:31.406
Even so, you need to eat.

00:17:36.899 --> 00:17:40.034
This has to be really hard on you, right?

00:17:41.208 --> 00:17:42.905
Woo Joo

00:17:42.905 --> 00:17:45.880
is probably having a harder time than I am.

00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:49.447
He was suddenly taken away from home

00:17:49.447 --> 00:17:51.796
and brought to a place he doesn't know.

00:17:53.512 --> 00:17:57.176
I really feel like I'm not enough for Woo Joo.

00:17:58.920 --> 00:18:00.394
I honestly don't know anymore

00:18:00.394 --> 00:18:03.391
whether I can really be someone

00:18:04.815 --> 00:18:07.186
who can fill his mom's place.

00:18:10.613 --> 00:18:12.947
I really wanted

00:18:12.947 --> 00:18:16.487
to be the kind of family
Woo Joo could truly rely on.

00:18:23.987 --> 00:18:26.837
You know, once you've lived a while,

00:18:26.837 --> 00:18:28.672
you learn that life doesn't always

00:18:28.672 --> 00:18:32.217
follow the path people expect.

00:18:32.217 --> 00:18:34.803
Take me and Doo Sik, for instance.

00:18:34.803 --> 00:18:40.344
Did you know we don't share any blood at all?

00:18:41.213 --> 00:18:42.507
Then...

00:18:42.507 --> 00:18:44.515
He's my son-in-law.

00:18:49.193 --> 00:18:51.014
She was in such a rush to leave this world

00:18:51.014 --> 00:18:54.650
that she passed away from an illness before me.

00:18:56.867 --> 00:19:00.156
Just getting through each day, just breathing,

00:19:03.791 --> 00:19:07.628
was so painful it felt like it would kill me.

00:19:07.628 --> 00:19:09.407
Then Doo Sik packed up his stuff

00:19:09.407 --> 00:19:11.905
and came barging in here out of nowhere, huh?

00:19:11.905 --> 00:19:13.114
He straight-up left his own home

00:19:13.114 --> 00:19:15.719
and settled down here of all places,

00:19:15.719 --> 00:19:17.249
keeping an eye on me,

00:19:17.249 --> 00:19:19.807
talking my ear off and driving me crazy.

00:19:19.807 --> 00:19:21.350
So I told him,

00:19:21.350 --> 00:19:23.421
"Your wife's gone,

00:19:23.421 --> 00:19:25.729
so why are you still here?
Have you lost your mind?"

00:19:25.729 --> 00:19:28.343
I'd cuss him out, whack him on the back,

00:19:28.343 --> 00:19:30.575
shove him off and tell him to get out,

00:19:30.575 --> 00:19:31.902
but he wouldn't move an inch.

00:19:31.902 --> 00:19:33.114
He'd just keep making silly jokes

00:19:33.114 --> 00:19:35.155
with that dumb grin on his face.

00:19:35.155 --> 00:19:37.199
He was so unbelievably stubborn that

00:19:37.199 --> 00:19:41.078
one day I looked him dead in the eye and said,

00:19:41.078 --> 00:19:42.955
"Why aren't you out living your own life?

00:19:42.955 --> 00:19:45.958
Why are you staying here with me?"

00:19:45.958 --> 00:19:47.912
And then he said,

00:19:49.086 --> 00:19:52.625
"As long as I'm here with you,

00:19:53.451 --> 00:19:56.670
this is my life."

00:19:57.747 --> 00:19:59.632
That's what he said to me.

00:20:01.751 --> 00:20:05.380
That's how Doo Sik held on tight to my hand

00:20:05.380 --> 00:20:07.549
and remained right here beside me,

00:20:07.549 --> 00:20:10.643
and became my family.

00:20:13.197 --> 00:20:16.530
So who says there are qualifications
for being family?

00:20:16.530 --> 00:20:19.489
Being sick with worry over Woo Joo
the way you are,

00:20:19.489 --> 00:20:23.280
fretting and stressing over him all day, huh?

00:20:23.280 --> 00:20:27.535
That's what makes someone family.

00:20:32.046 --> 00:20:34.131
Just look at me.

00:20:34.131 --> 00:20:38.739
To everyone else,
we probably seem like a pretty odd pair.

00:20:38.739 --> 00:20:40.137
My daughter's no longer here,

00:20:40.137 --> 00:20:43.223
but her husband and I still eat together,

00:20:43.223 --> 00:20:47.638
cry, laugh, squabble, and argue...

00:20:49.688 --> 00:20:51.231
But let me tell you something.

00:20:51.231 --> 00:20:53.776
Now that I've lived long enough to know,

00:20:53.776 --> 00:20:56.320
I've come to realize that's all it really is.

00:20:56.320 --> 00:21:01.111
Just sharing blood
doesn't make you family all by itself.

00:21:01.864 --> 00:21:04.620
It's those days

00:21:04.620 --> 00:21:07.947
when you keep each other going with love,

00:21:07.947 --> 00:21:12.836
and all those moments stacking up
little by little,

00:21:12.836 --> 00:21:15.291
that are what turn people into family.

00:21:16.131 --> 00:21:18.550
So as far as Woo Joo's concerned,

00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:22.513
you're already the steady, dependable mom
and family he can count on.

00:21:22.513 --> 00:21:24.973
So what do you think you're missing?
You're not missing a thing.

00:21:24.973 --> 00:21:26.433
Don't worry.

00:21:26.433 --> 00:21:29.144
You're already doing more than enough

00:21:29.144 --> 00:21:31.765
and handling it so well, okay?

00:21:34.817 --> 00:21:36.656
I'm really proud of you.

00:21:36.656 --> 00:21:38.987
You're doing such a good job.

00:21:38.987 --> 00:21:41.657
To Woo Joo, you're the one he has, okay?

00:21:41.657 --> 00:21:45.488
So hold your head up, come on, have a bite.

00:21:55.901 --> 00:21:57.444
Where were you?

00:21:57.444 --> 00:22:01.086
Oh, I went to grab a few things.

00:22:04.159 --> 00:22:05.619
What are you doing?

00:22:05.619 --> 00:22:08.005
I'm just stepping out for a bit.

00:22:08.005 --> 00:22:10.207
Right now? To where?

00:22:10.207 --> 00:22:12.918
Woo Joo doesn't sleep well by himself.

00:22:12.918 --> 00:22:15.518
He has to be scared without us there.

00:22:16.588 --> 00:22:18.173
So I figured maybe

00:22:18.173 --> 00:22:20.675
this could make it a little easier.

00:22:20.675 --> 00:22:22.691
Let's go together.

00:22:26.014 --> 00:22:27.565
- Hand it over. I'll take it.
- Okay.

00:22:27.565 --> 00:22:29.323
Here you go.

00:22:30.518 --> 00:22:33.355
Woo Joo looked like he might be coming down
with a cold yesterday,

00:22:33.355 --> 00:22:34.773
so I brought these just in case,

00:22:34.773 --> 00:22:37.943
some fever medicine and cold medicine.

00:22:37.943 --> 00:22:40.570
And Woo Joo's skin is really sensitive,

00:22:40.570 --> 00:22:42.447
so his diaper rash can flare up pretty badly.

00:22:42.447 --> 00:22:45.992
Could you please make sure

00:22:45.992 --> 00:22:48.425
that he uses only this kind of diaper?

00:22:49.412 --> 00:22:51.164
And...

00:22:51.164 --> 00:22:54.459
this is Woo Joo's favorite comfort doll.

00:22:54.459 --> 00:22:57.003
He was probably badly shaken up,

00:22:57.003 --> 00:22:58.838
so I thought maybe if he had this with him,

00:22:58.838 --> 00:23:01.063
it might help him feel a little better.

00:23:01.681 --> 00:23:03.426
If you can, please put him to bed by nine.

00:23:03.426 --> 00:23:05.262
That will probably make things easier.

00:23:05.262 --> 00:23:09.474
Once he misses that bedtime window,
he tends to fight sleep.

00:23:09.474 --> 00:23:10.558
Oh, and one more thing.

00:23:10.558 --> 00:23:14.579
Sometimes he cries looking for his mom and dad.

00:23:14.579 --> 00:23:17.232
When that happens,
just hold him and pat him gently,

00:23:17.232 --> 00:23:19.234
and he should settle down pretty fast.

00:23:19.234 --> 00:23:20.652
Understood.

00:23:20.652 --> 00:23:22.112
Please don't worry too much.

00:23:22.112 --> 00:23:24.864
It's only for a short while,

00:23:24.864 --> 00:23:27.826
so please take good care of our Woo Joo.

00:23:27.826 --> 00:23:29.911
Please look after him well.

00:23:29.911 --> 00:23:31.563
Yes.

00:23:33.999 --> 00:23:36.418
I seriously don't have any appetite.

00:23:36.418 --> 00:23:40.234
At a time like this, you've got to eat right
so you can stay strong.

00:23:41.715 --> 00:23:45.399
You still haven't had a single thing
to eat since yesterday.

00:23:53.476 --> 00:23:55.444
Here.

00:23:59.899 --> 00:24:03.083
Do you remember that time?

00:24:03.868 --> 00:24:05.530
Back at the columbarium before,

00:24:05.530 --> 00:24:09.075
when you asked me
whether I'd ever consider taking in Woo Joo,

00:24:09.075 --> 00:24:10.827
and I told you

00:24:10.827 --> 00:24:14.164
that I'm not someone who's capable
of being responsible for somebody else?

00:24:14.164 --> 00:24:15.707
Of course I do.

00:24:15.707 --> 00:24:17.459
How would I ever forget something like that?

00:24:17.459 --> 00:24:18.668
Back then,

00:24:18.668 --> 00:24:21.338
I honestly thought that was who I was.

00:24:21.338 --> 00:24:24.090
I believed I was someone
who couldn't be responsible for anybody,

00:24:24.090 --> 00:24:25.967
much less know how to give someone

00:24:25.967 --> 00:24:28.317
the love they truly deserve.

00:24:30.055 --> 00:24:32.015
Honestly, if you hadn't been in my life,

00:24:32.015 --> 00:24:34.691
I probably would've spent my whole life
never figuring that out.

00:24:34.691 --> 00:24:36.144
You just saw it with your own eyes.

00:24:36.144 --> 00:24:38.521
No matter how hard or terrifying things get,

00:24:38.521 --> 00:24:40.648
Woo Joo is always the first one on your mind.

00:24:40.648 --> 00:24:42.275
You said this to me before,

00:24:42.275 --> 00:24:43.902
that whenever things start to shake me,

00:24:43.902 --> 00:24:47.113
I should trust you

00:24:47.113 --> 00:24:48.990
who has faith in me.

00:24:48.990 --> 00:24:52.077
So now, I'm asking you to believe in me.

00:24:52.077 --> 00:24:54.037
Because I truly believe

00:24:54.037 --> 00:24:57.457
you're absolutely good enough
to be Woo Joo's guardian.

00:24:57.457 --> 00:24:59.876
You don't need to wear yourself out
trying to handle everything by yourself.

00:24:59.876 --> 00:25:01.155
Sometimes, when you can't do it all,

00:25:01.155 --> 00:25:03.213
I'll step in and make up the difference.

00:25:03.213 --> 00:25:04.506
And sometimes,

00:25:04.506 --> 00:25:07.675
you'll be the one covering for me.

00:25:07.675 --> 00:25:09.427
We just need to make it through together.

00:25:09.427 --> 00:25:10.845
Right?

00:25:10.845 --> 00:25:12.653
Thank you.

00:25:20.980 --> 00:25:24.651
I can't live without Woo Joo anymore either.

00:25:24.651 --> 00:25:25.823
We're Woo Joo's family,

00:25:25.823 --> 00:25:28.154
so how can they just take Woo Joo
away from us like this?

00:25:28.154 --> 00:25:29.531
That's right.

00:25:29.531 --> 00:25:31.074
Because we're Woo Joo's family.

00:25:31.074 --> 00:25:33.743
We're going to make that clear
no matter what it takes,

00:25:33.743 --> 00:25:35.703
so eat up and get your strength back,

00:25:35.703 --> 00:25:37.580
and then let's start doing what we need to do.

00:25:37.580 --> 00:25:39.215
Okay.

00:25:40.959 --> 00:25:42.252
From what I've heard,

00:25:42.252 --> 00:25:43.711
the important thing is

00:25:43.711 --> 00:25:46.339
the safety steps we added
after the accident happened.

00:25:46.339 --> 00:25:48.383
They said that's how we can show
that this wasn't neglect,

00:25:48.383 --> 00:25:50.718
it was an accident.

00:25:50.718 --> 00:25:54.355
So I went and picked up
some baby gates and a home camera.

00:25:55.890 --> 00:25:57.273
Thank you.

00:25:57.273 --> 00:25:59.125
It's reassuring to have you here.

00:26:07.986 --> 00:26:10.822
The place feels so empty without Woo Joo here.

00:26:10.822 --> 00:26:12.031
Let's pull everything back together

00:26:12.031 --> 00:26:13.533
and bring Woo Joo back home.

00:26:13.533 --> 00:26:14.965
Okay.

00:26:22.834 --> 00:26:24.210
So, are you saying

00:26:24.210 --> 00:26:25.795
Woo Joo has been taken away from you for now?

00:26:25.795 --> 00:26:27.213
My head's been all over the place,

00:26:27.213 --> 00:26:28.631
so I only just noticed you called.

00:26:28.631 --> 00:26:30.550
Oh, that explains it.

00:26:30.550 --> 00:26:32.552
You suddenly told me you were taking a day off,

00:26:32.552 --> 00:26:34.387
so I got concerned and gave you a call.

00:26:34.387 --> 00:26:36.097
So what's happening right now?

00:26:36.097 --> 00:26:37.474
Is there anything I can do for you?

00:26:37.474 --> 00:26:39.559
No, I'm good. To get Woo Joo back

00:26:39.559 --> 00:26:41.197
and also get through the guardianship review,

00:26:41.197 --> 00:26:43.021
we have to go through a home visit,

00:26:43.021 --> 00:26:45.356
so I was just getting the house in order.

00:26:45.356 --> 00:26:47.706
This must be really hard on you.

00:26:48.776 --> 00:26:52.238
Are you holding up okay?

00:26:52.238 --> 00:26:53.740
Of course.

00:26:53.740 --> 00:26:57.243
I'm only trying
to focus on bringing Woo Joo back.

00:26:57.243 --> 00:26:59.078
Okay.

00:26:59.078 --> 00:27:01.331
If you need anything from me,

00:27:01.331 --> 00:27:02.916
just call anytime.

00:27:02.916 --> 00:27:05.891
Yes, thank you.

00:27:18.681 --> 00:27:20.600
Hey, it's me.

00:27:20.600 --> 00:27:23.192
Yeah, I've been well.

00:27:23.192 --> 00:27:27.397
I just wanted to ask you something.

00:27:27.397 --> 00:27:30.874
I was wondering if you knew anything
about child separation procedures.

00:27:31.486 --> 00:27:33.613
You're going to fix up the house?

00:27:33.613 --> 00:27:36.330
What parts of the place
are you trying to work on?

00:27:36.330 --> 00:27:37.874
I'm planning to install a home camera,

00:27:37.874 --> 00:27:39.827
and put up a safety fence for the baby too.

00:27:39.827 --> 00:27:42.789
Well, that's exactly
what this neighborhood MacGyver does best.

00:27:42.789 --> 00:27:43.831
Do you want me to help out?

00:27:43.831 --> 00:27:46.334
For real? We'd be really grateful for that.

00:27:46.334 --> 00:27:48.155
No need to thank me.
Want me to throw this garbage away?

00:27:48.155 --> 00:27:50.364
It's okay. I'll take care of it.

00:27:50.364 --> 00:27:52.563
Stay inside. I'll go.

00:27:53.967 --> 00:27:55.552
All right, it's done.

00:27:55.552 --> 00:27:57.143
Is the home cam working?

00:27:57.143 --> 00:27:58.921
Does it make me look handsome or what?

00:27:58.921 --> 00:28:00.313
No, I mean the camera picture
looks really clear.

00:28:00.313 --> 00:28:01.364
Good grief.

00:28:01.364 --> 00:28:03.985
- What about you?
- Me? I made sure it was put together right.

00:28:03.985 --> 00:28:05.693
Who do you think you're talking to?

00:28:05.693 --> 00:28:07.656
I'm the MacGyver around here.

00:28:07.656 --> 00:28:09.581
Hyun Jin.

00:28:10.191 --> 00:28:11.574
Oh, my.

00:28:11.574 --> 00:28:14.279
- Geez.
- I'm sorry. Just a second.

00:28:14.279 --> 00:28:15.488
I heard you were doing some work on the house,

00:28:15.488 --> 00:28:17.163
so I brought some stuff by.

00:28:17.163 --> 00:28:19.114
Some of it's what Bom and Yeo Reum used before,

00:28:19.114 --> 00:28:21.035
and some of it was given to me as presents.

00:28:21.035 --> 00:28:23.079
- Thank you.
- Oh, it's nothing.

00:28:23.079 --> 00:28:25.540
When we're both raising kids,
helping each other out is just what you do.

00:28:25.540 --> 00:28:26.583
Anyway,

00:28:26.583 --> 00:28:28.334
I checked a moms' online community,

00:28:28.334 --> 00:28:30.781
and they said the key thing
to getting the separation order lifted

00:28:30.781 --> 00:28:33.506
is having solid objective evidence.

00:28:33.506 --> 00:28:35.272
Evidence?

00:28:36.840 --> 00:28:37.844
What is that?

00:28:37.844 --> 00:28:39.220
I think this might help the investigator

00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:40.489
and the police see the situation differently.

00:28:40.489 --> 00:28:41.681
What is it?

00:28:41.681 --> 00:28:43.391
It's a recorded call.

00:28:43.391 --> 00:28:45.018
What made you call?

00:28:45.018 --> 00:28:47.527
Oh, hello. Woo Joo suddenly
started running a fever,

00:28:47.527 --> 00:28:49.063
so I wanted to ask whether you had

00:28:49.063 --> 00:28:50.690
any fever medicine at home.

00:28:50.690 --> 00:28:52.609
- I'm out right now.
- Wouldn't this back up the argument

00:28:52.609 --> 00:28:53.985
that you were not intentionally
neglecting Woo Joo,

00:28:53.985 --> 00:28:55.988
and were just panicking

00:28:55.988 --> 00:28:56.988
while trying to find medicine?

00:28:56.988 --> 00:28:57.912
- Yeah.
- You're right.

00:28:57.912 --> 00:28:59.988
Your voice was trembling the whole time.

00:28:59.988 --> 00:29:01.030
It's obvious that you were really worried.

00:29:01.030 --> 00:29:02.869
This really could count as evidence.
You did well.

00:29:02.869 --> 00:29:04.120
Exactly.

00:29:04.120 --> 00:29:05.163
This should definitely help as evidence.

00:29:05.163 --> 00:29:06.247
Nice work.

00:29:06.247 --> 00:29:08.458
When you've got a child, anything can happen

00:29:08.458 --> 00:29:10.585
in the blink of an eye.

00:29:10.585 --> 00:29:11.676
If you bring this along,

00:29:11.676 --> 00:29:13.719
I'm sure it'll help them
understand what happened.

00:29:13.719 --> 00:29:14.922
Thank you, seriously.

00:29:14.922 --> 00:29:17.216
You've all done so much for me.

00:29:17.216 --> 00:29:18.718
I really can't thank you enough.

00:29:18.718 --> 00:29:21.143
Oh, it's really nothing.

00:29:21.143 --> 00:29:22.643
All right.

00:29:22.643 --> 00:29:24.098
So what do we do first?

00:29:24.098 --> 00:29:26.228
- Buy us a meal.
- But what is this?

00:29:26.228 --> 00:29:29.618
- You knocked this over.
- This goes on the wall.

00:29:37.236 --> 00:29:39.489
[Attorney Kim Seung Eon]
I thought you were swamped.

00:29:39.489 --> 00:29:42.492
So what brings you all the way out here?

00:29:42.492 --> 00:29:44.619
I came because I wanted
to check how things were going.

00:29:44.619 --> 00:29:46.412
- This, right?
- Yeah.

00:29:46.412 --> 00:29:47.864
Actually, I just sent the documents

00:29:47.864 --> 00:29:49.415
to the police and the appropriate agency.

00:29:49.415 --> 00:29:51.000
You'll see when you read it,

00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:53.419
but all the statements,
from the people in the villa

00:29:53.419 --> 00:29:56.047
to the daycare teacher,
are in Woo Hyun Jin's favor.

00:29:56.047 --> 00:29:59.133
Looks like the aunt really doted on the child.

00:29:59.133 --> 00:30:00.551
So that means everything's okay, right?

00:30:00.551 --> 00:30:03.402
It doesn't look
like you need to worry that much.

00:30:04.180 --> 00:30:05.473
Thanks.

00:30:05.473 --> 00:30:07.392
I'll treat you to a meal soon.

00:30:07.392 --> 00:30:10.492
Then you'd better make it
somewhere pricey, okay?

00:30:11.938 --> 00:30:13.606
But who is she, anyway?

00:30:13.606 --> 00:30:14.941
Who exactly is she

00:30:14.941 --> 00:30:17.276
that you would personally
step in for her like this?

00:30:17.276 --> 00:30:20.043
Is she your girlfriend or something?

00:30:21.781 --> 00:30:23.783
No.

00:30:23.783 --> 00:30:25.674
She's my first love.

00:30:28.044 --> 00:30:29.638
Mommy.

00:30:31.373 --> 00:30:36.059
Why do you keep crying like this?
Baby, isn't this hard on you?

00:30:40.556 --> 00:30:43.643
- We need to be strict about this.
- Woo Joo?

00:30:43.643 --> 00:30:45.930
Okay, I'll get back to you.

00:30:45.930 --> 00:30:47.696
All right.

00:30:49.767 --> 00:30:51.947
Why? Is something wrong?

00:30:51.947 --> 00:30:53.312
Well...

00:30:53.312 --> 00:30:55.356
Sounds like the kid hasn't slept in days

00:30:55.356 --> 00:30:57.150
and won't stop crying.

00:30:57.150 --> 00:31:00.278
He keeps looking for his aunt and uncle.

00:31:00.278 --> 00:31:04.421
Those two really
put their whole hearts into it.

00:31:05.070 --> 00:31:07.994
You can tell just from this petition alone.

00:31:07.994 --> 00:31:09.454
Anyway,

00:31:09.454 --> 00:31:11.456
the police said their investigation is over,

00:31:11.456 --> 00:31:12.582
and we've already forwarded

00:31:12.582 --> 00:31:14.459
our report to the local government,

00:31:14.459 --> 00:31:16.676
so we should be hearing back pretty soon.

00:31:16.676 --> 00:31:19.387
Would it be okay if I saw that?

00:31:19.387 --> 00:31:21.899
Of course.

00:31:24.343 --> 00:31:25.887
Sorry I'm late.

00:31:25.887 --> 00:31:27.930
What?

00:31:27.930 --> 00:31:29.640
Weren't you supposed
to be off for half the day?

00:31:29.640 --> 00:31:31.107
You still had a lot of time left.

00:31:31.107 --> 00:31:32.435
How come you're back already?

00:31:32.435 --> 00:31:33.728
I've got too much work piled up,

00:31:33.728 --> 00:31:35.197
and I've already used
a half day and vacation time

00:31:35.197 --> 00:31:36.564
one after another these past few days.

00:31:36.564 --> 00:31:38.024
Come on.

00:31:38.024 --> 00:31:40.234
Why are you saying sorry
for using your own time off?

00:31:40.234 --> 00:31:43.001
You're secretly way too uptight.

00:31:44.912 --> 00:31:45.579
[Planning Team 3 Manager Park Yoon Seong]

00:31:45.579 --> 00:31:48.659
That's consistent with
what you told us earlier.

00:31:48.659 --> 00:31:51.078
I looked over the petition this morning,

00:31:51.078 --> 00:31:54.332
and it made me think this must've
all started from a misunderstanding.

00:31:54.332 --> 00:31:55.614
When a case involves a child,

00:31:55.614 --> 00:31:57.258
it's an extremely sensitive matter,

00:31:57.258 --> 00:31:59.170
so sometimes a brief misunderstanding

00:31:59.170 --> 00:32:01.881
can result in excessive action like this.

00:32:01.881 --> 00:32:04.509
A petition?

00:32:04.509 --> 00:32:06.052
Oh, right.

00:32:06.052 --> 00:32:07.970
It's a written petition
stating that the abuse claims

00:32:07.970 --> 00:32:10.348
[A petition]
against her came from a misunderstanding.

00:32:10.348 --> 00:32:13.059
As you know, in cases like these,

00:32:13.059 --> 00:32:14.692
a report or statement from a third party

00:32:14.692 --> 00:32:16.979
can serve as important evidence.

00:32:16.979 --> 00:32:19.106
But who submitted it?

00:32:19.106 --> 00:32:21.692
Oh? You hadn't heard?

00:32:21.692 --> 00:32:23.909
A man named Park Yoon Seong

00:32:23.909 --> 00:32:25.828
also filed a written statement.

00:32:25.828 --> 00:32:27.122
[People Who Signed the Petition]

00:32:28.456 --> 00:32:29.999
[Park Yoon Seong]

00:32:29.999 --> 00:32:31.599
[Planning Team 3 Manager Park Yoon Seong]

00:32:36.249 --> 00:32:37.834
Weren't you just working a half day today?

00:32:37.834 --> 00:32:38.835
You got here pretty early.

00:32:38.835 --> 00:32:40.336
Oh, sir.

00:32:40.336 --> 00:32:42.505
Is the manager out right now?

00:32:42.505 --> 00:32:44.382
I heard he'll be out on business all day.

00:32:44.382 --> 00:32:46.217
Seems like that overseas expo

00:32:46.217 --> 00:32:48.135
is turning into something bigger than expected.

00:32:48.135 --> 00:32:49.387
I heard it's a project even the U.S. branch

00:32:49.387 --> 00:32:51.695
has been eager to take on.

00:32:53.647 --> 00:32:56.486
I really should thank him.

00:33:00.231 --> 00:33:02.656
Hello?

00:33:02.656 --> 00:33:04.368
What?

00:33:05.403 --> 00:33:08.322
Thank you. I really appreciate it.

00:33:08.322 --> 00:33:10.700
Come here, Woo Joo.

00:33:10.700 --> 00:33:12.410
Woo Joo.

00:33:15.211 --> 00:33:18.091
Thank goodness he isn't running a fever.
Now, look at me.

00:33:18.833 --> 00:33:22.267
Do you know how badly I wanted to see you?

00:33:24.263 --> 00:33:25.840
Thank you.

00:33:25.840 --> 00:33:26.883
It was nothing.

00:33:26.883 --> 00:33:28.968
I'm here to wrap up

00:33:28.968 --> 00:33:31.193
the home visit we didn't get to do last time.

00:34:11.697 --> 00:34:13.356
[I made toast,
so make sure you eat before you leave]

00:34:13.356 --> 00:34:14.808
[Trash day today! Don't forget the recycling!]

00:34:31.489 --> 00:34:33.074
Woo Joo's aunt?

00:34:33.074 --> 00:34:35.159
[Saetbyeol Daycare]
There must've been some misunderstanding.

00:34:35.159 --> 00:34:37.459
Woo Joo, whenever his aunt picks him up,

00:34:37.459 --> 00:34:38.460
he gets so happy he practically starts flying.

00:34:38.460 --> 00:34:40.873
If anything, his aunt and uncle
fuss over him too much.

00:34:40.873 --> 00:34:42.708
It is nowhere near neglect.

00:34:42.708 --> 00:34:44.377
Mothers can tell at a glance.

00:34:44.377 --> 00:34:45.753
You always feel sorry toward your child,

00:34:45.753 --> 00:34:47.213
like whatever you do still is not enough.

00:34:47.213 --> 00:34:48.405
That is exactly what Woo Joo's aunt is like.

00:34:48.405 --> 00:34:49.430
Isn't that what a mother's heart is like?

00:34:49.430 --> 00:34:52.093
There is nobody who thinks about Woo Joo
more than his aunt does.

00:34:52.093 --> 00:34:54.595
Just think about that day.
She ran out with her shoes on wrong,

00:34:54.595 --> 00:34:55.972
crying her eyes out.

00:34:55.972 --> 00:34:57.056
Even I feel upset over how unfair this is.

00:34:57.056 --> 00:34:59.684
Those people are already family.

00:34:59.684 --> 00:35:01.769
What else even needs to be said?

00:35:01.769 --> 00:35:03.030
Please, counselor.

00:35:03.030 --> 00:35:05.106
Please handle this case well for us.

00:35:05.106 --> 00:35:07.110
I'd put my name on this
a hundred times if I had to.

00:35:07.110 --> 00:35:08.609
[Petition Signature List]

00:35:08.609 --> 00:35:10.405
Whether I see her as a boss or a senior,

00:35:10.405 --> 00:35:13.280
or simply as one human being to another,

00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:15.366
Hyun Jin is genuinely a good person.

00:35:15.366 --> 00:35:18.285
She's caring
and has a strong sense of responsibility,

00:35:18.285 --> 00:35:20.294
so please help her.

00:35:20.294 --> 00:35:23.596
[A petition]

00:35:24.924 --> 00:35:26.766
[A petition]

00:35:35.559 --> 00:35:37.680
And this is the childcare album

00:35:37.680 --> 00:35:39.405
that Woo Joo's uncle brought with him.

00:35:39.405 --> 00:35:41.364
[Woo Joo's fever wouldn't go down.
I wish I could be sick instead]

00:35:41.364 --> 00:35:43.373
[Woo Joo finished all his food today.
I'm so happy]

00:35:49.406 --> 00:35:53.279
[All of us at Beopgi Reservoir]

00:35:53.279 --> 00:35:58.117
[You are my universe]
Honestly, these pictures made it clear to me.

00:35:58.117 --> 00:35:59.994
You can tell just by looking at her

00:35:59.994 --> 00:36:01.662
how much she loves that child.

00:36:01.662 --> 00:36:04.165
And the way that child receives her love

00:36:04.165 --> 00:36:06.431
looks completely natural to him.

00:36:11.505 --> 00:36:15.259
Woo Joo really loves you.

00:36:15.259 --> 00:36:17.553
I think we've done enough for today.

00:36:17.553 --> 00:36:20.070
I'll see you at the hearing.

00:36:26.854 --> 00:36:29.573
- Get home safe.
- Okay.

00:36:31.405 --> 00:36:32.947
Woo Joo.

00:36:32.947 --> 00:36:34.988
I really missed you.

00:36:34.988 --> 00:36:36.322
I missed you so much.

00:36:36.322 --> 00:36:37.531
Are you all right?

00:36:37.531 --> 00:36:39.506
I missed you.

00:36:58.552 --> 00:37:00.387
He smells like a baby.

00:37:00.387 --> 00:37:02.723
Nice, isn't it?

00:37:02.723 --> 00:37:05.226
He's usually a fighter,

00:37:05.226 --> 00:37:07.617
but right now,
anyone could just carry him away.

00:37:08.277 --> 00:37:10.154
Exactly.

00:37:10.154 --> 00:37:13.832
Our Woo Joo really went through a lot.

00:37:15.611 --> 00:37:18.628
You went through a lot, too.

00:37:20.538 --> 00:37:22.368
I wasn't the only one who went through a lot.

00:37:22.368 --> 00:37:23.536
Honestly, I wish

00:37:23.536 --> 00:37:26.261
I'd been the only one hurting through all this.

00:37:27.289 --> 00:37:30.473
You shouldn't say that. We're family.

00:37:32.545 --> 00:37:35.214
I'm thinking maybe Woo Joo and I

00:37:35.214 --> 00:37:38.773
should stay in the bedroom
instead of living out in the living room.

00:37:40.636 --> 00:37:41.935
Really?

00:37:41.935 --> 00:37:44.607
I looked into it this time,

00:37:45.349 --> 00:37:47.351
and they say when a child's sleeping space

00:37:47.351 --> 00:37:49.770
and play area are not separated,

00:37:49.770 --> 00:37:50.823
it can make it harder

00:37:50.823 --> 00:37:53.413
for the child to fall asleep.

00:37:54.406 --> 00:37:55.484
They also say that even if it is not big,

00:37:55.484 --> 00:37:57.611
having a space they can clearly call their own

00:37:57.611 --> 00:37:59.989
is better for them emotionally.

00:37:59.989 --> 00:38:02.297
I mean, that makes sense,

00:38:02.992 --> 00:38:04.785
but are you sure you're okay with it?

00:38:04.785 --> 00:38:06.162
At first,

00:38:06.162 --> 00:38:09.623
whenever I thought
about my sister, I would cry,

00:38:09.623 --> 00:38:13.155
and it was painful because I kept remembering
all the times I acted badly toward her.

00:38:13.155 --> 00:38:14.879
But that is not how it is now.

00:38:14.879 --> 00:38:17.256
Even if she is not here with me anymore,

00:38:17.256 --> 00:38:20.384
the love she gave me

00:38:20.384 --> 00:38:22.678
and all the time we shared together

00:38:22.678 --> 00:38:26.223
are still living on inside me.

00:38:26.223 --> 00:38:28.072
Come here.

00:38:28.976 --> 00:38:31.493
Let me give you a hug.

00:38:34.690 --> 00:38:37.373
Thank you.

00:38:45.040 --> 00:38:47.660
[Seoul Family Court] [Seoul Admin Court]

00:38:48.579 --> 00:38:51.165
Man, this is making me nervous too.

00:38:51.165 --> 00:38:54.599
It's going to go well.
Why are you stressing so much?

00:39:03.851 --> 00:39:05.769
Why are you acting like that?
It's embarrassing.

00:39:05.769 --> 00:39:07.447
You're making the kids do the same thing.

00:39:07.447 --> 00:39:09.808
- Quiet. I think I hear something.
- What?

00:39:09.808 --> 00:39:10.893
I said I hear something. Come on.

00:39:10.893 --> 00:39:12.069
- Come on, quick.
- Can you hear it?

00:39:12.069 --> 00:39:13.938
- This is a case
- Can you hear it?

00:39:13.938 --> 00:39:15.606
that has to be decided with the child's safety

00:39:15.606 --> 00:39:16.607
and well-being

00:39:16.607 --> 00:39:18.692
placed above all else.

00:39:18.692 --> 00:39:20.486
Because this decision

00:39:20.486 --> 00:39:23.996
will affect the child's entire
living environment,

00:39:23.996 --> 00:39:27.409
the court examined the case very carefully.

00:39:27.409 --> 00:39:30.537
The documents you turned in,
the interview details,

00:39:30.537 --> 00:39:32.317
[Judge's bench]
and the family investigation results

00:39:32.317 --> 00:39:34.083
have all been taken into consideration.

00:39:34.083 --> 00:39:36.627
As a result, the court finds

00:39:36.627 --> 00:39:38.337
the guardian candidate to be the most stable

00:39:38.337 --> 00:39:41.396
and appropriate person to care for the child.

00:39:42.841 --> 00:39:45.149
For that reason, this court

00:39:47.686 --> 00:39:50.441
grants the petition to appoint

00:39:51.809 --> 00:39:54.033
guardian candidate Woo Hyun Jin

00:39:54.895 --> 00:39:56.786
as the child's legal guardian.

00:40:04.238 --> 00:40:05.531
Woo Joo, it got approved.

00:40:05.531 --> 00:40:08.041
- They approved it.
- Yeah.

00:40:08.707 --> 00:40:09.743
I think it got approved.

00:40:09.743 --> 00:40:11.120
Don't say "I think."
Tell me if it was approved or not.

00:40:11.120 --> 00:40:12.413
It sounds like it got approved.

00:40:12.413 --> 00:40:14.039
So was it approved or not?
Don't keep saying "I think."

00:40:14.039 --> 00:40:15.499
Just tell me straight if it got approved.

00:40:15.499 --> 00:40:16.917
Wait. How did it turn out?

00:40:16.917 --> 00:40:19.420
How did it go?

00:40:19.420 --> 00:40:21.672
It was approved.

00:40:21.672 --> 00:40:25.148
Yes! Hooray!

00:40:27.155 --> 00:40:29.030
Woo Joo!

00:40:29.030 --> 00:40:32.391
- You really went through a lot.
- Woo Joo!

00:40:32.391 --> 00:40:36.367
- Long live Yooseong Villa!
- Hooray!

00:40:37.438 --> 00:40:39.898
Thank you all so much.

00:40:39.898 --> 00:40:43.916
The two of us
never could've come this far by ourselves.

00:40:46.363 --> 00:40:47.781
Thank you.

00:40:47.781 --> 00:40:49.248
We won't forget what you've done for us,

00:40:49.248 --> 00:40:51.076
and we'll make sure to return it twofold.

00:40:51.076 --> 00:40:53.412
You don't need some grand gesture
to repay us, right?

00:40:53.412 --> 00:40:55.489
Just make sure our Woo Joo

00:40:55.489 --> 00:40:57.791
grows up healthy and well, all right?

00:40:57.791 --> 00:40:59.925
And you two need to quit arguing

00:40:59.925 --> 00:41:01.239
and just live together in peace.

00:41:01.239 --> 00:41:03.130
That alone is more than enough to repay us.

00:41:03.130 --> 00:41:04.905
- Wouldn't you say so?
- Well...

00:41:04.905 --> 00:41:07.426
I'm saying this
because you want to return the favor.

00:41:07.426 --> 00:41:09.489
We came all the way out here,

00:41:09.489 --> 00:41:10.936
and we ended up skipping lunch.

00:41:10.936 --> 00:41:14.600
My mom can't stand it when she skips mealtime.

00:41:14.600 --> 00:41:17.102
- All right, let's go then.
- What?

00:41:17.102 --> 00:41:18.155
I'll buy everyone something good to eat.

00:41:18.155 --> 00:41:20.391
For real?

00:41:20.872 --> 00:41:22.625
- Meat! Meat!
- Meat!

00:41:22.625 --> 00:41:26.585
- Beef!
- Beef!

00:41:26.585 --> 00:41:29.880
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

00:41:29.880 --> 00:41:31.205
There we go.

00:41:31.205 --> 00:41:33.008
Got it.

00:41:33.008 --> 00:41:36.205
- Should we check?
- Want to look at how the pictures turned out?

00:41:36.205 --> 00:41:37.896
This one.

00:41:39.681 --> 00:41:40.810
It looks really good.

00:41:40.810 --> 00:41:43.227
Great.

00:41:43.227 --> 00:41:45.581
All right, now we just wait.

00:41:45.581 --> 00:41:47.530
It's done.

00:41:48.247 --> 00:41:49.441
If I knew this would happen,

00:41:49.441 --> 00:41:50.914
I would've at least
brought my camera from the office.

00:41:50.914 --> 00:41:52.830
Why? These already came out great.

00:41:52.830 --> 00:41:55.948
Even so, I'm the uncle who's a photographer.

00:41:55.948 --> 00:41:58.539
My pride is at stake here.

00:41:58.539 --> 00:42:00.413
It's just a kid's homework. What reputation?

00:42:00.413 --> 00:42:02.497
Right, Woo Joo?

00:42:02.497 --> 00:42:03.955
What is it?

00:42:03.955 --> 00:42:05.637
- Red.
- Red?

00:42:11.456 --> 00:42:13.264
Blue.

00:42:15.855 --> 00:42:17.769
White.

00:42:23.773 --> 00:42:25.269
See? It turned out nicely, didn't it?

00:42:25.269 --> 00:42:27.153
Hand it to your aunt.

00:42:28.080 --> 00:42:29.497
The picture is super clear.

00:42:29.497 --> 00:42:30.705
Right?

00:42:30.705 --> 00:42:32.025
It really did come out well.

00:42:32.025 --> 00:42:34.289
This is really convenient to use.

00:42:34.289 --> 00:42:36.664
But come on, why does a kid this young

00:42:36.664 --> 00:42:38.539
already have homework?

00:42:38.539 --> 00:42:42.794
Our Woo Joo shouldn't be
dealing with stress already, okay?

00:42:45.872 --> 00:42:48.667
He takes off the moment we mention homework.

00:42:48.667 --> 00:42:50.586
- Woo Joo really knows how to have fun.
- Yeah.

00:42:50.586 --> 00:42:51.737
Okay, get up now.

00:42:51.737 --> 00:42:52.755
Why?

00:42:52.755 --> 00:42:54.131
What kind of question is that?

00:42:54.131 --> 00:42:56.643
We agreed to finish cleaning the bedroom.

00:42:57.787 --> 00:42:59.205
Honey.

00:42:59.205 --> 00:43:00.872
Can we stay like this a bit longer?

00:43:00.872 --> 00:43:03.348
What is with the "honey"?
Are you out of your mind?

00:43:03.348 --> 00:43:04.539
What's wrong?

00:43:04.539 --> 00:43:06.894
I just want a little more time

00:43:06.894 --> 00:43:09.112
like this with you.

00:43:11.231 --> 00:43:13.901
Oh, quit it. You're making me blush.

00:43:13.901 --> 00:43:16.197
Honey.

00:43:20.413 --> 00:43:22.117
All done.

00:43:23.080 --> 00:43:25.211
Is there anything left to take care of?

00:43:30.334 --> 00:43:32.594
Thank you.

00:43:39.218 --> 00:43:41.811
Why are you acting like this out of nowhere?

00:43:43.539 --> 00:43:45.140
It's just that...

00:43:45.140 --> 00:43:49.063
Just seeing you here with me

00:43:49.063 --> 00:43:50.604
in this house

00:43:50.604 --> 00:43:52.835
fills me with happiness all over again.

00:43:57.539 --> 00:43:59.738
How about we take a family photo?

00:43:59.738 --> 00:44:00.823
A family photo?

00:44:02.456 --> 00:44:06.377
We should take one with Woo Joo, you, and me

00:44:13.085 --> 00:44:15.595
and put it up right beside this photo.

00:44:19.049 --> 00:44:20.581
You know if we take a family picture,

00:44:20.581 --> 00:44:23.227
that means we have
to stay family forever, right?

00:44:26.557 --> 00:44:28.524
Goodness.

00:44:31.436 --> 00:44:32.909
What?

00:44:32.909 --> 00:44:35.691
You just kissed me
and you're not going to answer?

00:44:35.691 --> 00:44:38.743
So you're really not going to answer me?

00:44:48.955 --> 00:44:50.672
I love you.

00:44:51.957 --> 00:44:54.001
Thank you for staying by my side

00:44:54.001 --> 00:44:56.552
and for being my home.

00:45:06.205 --> 00:45:08.272
I love you too.

00:45:17.414 --> 00:45:20.039
Let's run away.

00:45:20.039 --> 00:45:22.195
No.

00:45:22.195 --> 00:45:28.076
You can't get away.

00:45:28.076 --> 00:45:29.247
Yoon Seong.

00:45:29.247 --> 00:45:31.121
Have you really made up your mind?

00:45:31.121 --> 00:45:32.247
The U.S. branch also said

00:45:32.247 --> 00:45:35.164
they need a person in charge
of the overseas expo project,

00:45:35.164 --> 00:45:36.875
so it feels like a really good opportunity
from every angle.

00:45:36.875 --> 00:45:40.255
I know it's a great chance for you,

00:45:40.255 --> 00:45:42.049
but I'm the one who feels bad about losing you.

00:45:42.049 --> 00:45:43.926
If you head over to the U.S. branch,

00:45:43.926 --> 00:45:45.886
who's supposed to take your place here?

00:45:45.886 --> 00:45:47.390
I'm really going to feel your absence.

00:45:47.390 --> 00:45:50.481
I owe it all to the way
you guided me, Director.

00:45:55.320 --> 00:45:57.071
Hyun Jin.

00:45:57.731 --> 00:45:59.027
Yoon Seong.

00:45:59.027 --> 00:46:02.410
Do you have a minute?

00:46:06.448 --> 00:46:08.700
I was actually meaning to talk to you too.

00:46:08.700 --> 00:46:11.536
Then why don't you go first?

00:46:11.536 --> 00:46:14.297
No, you first.

00:46:16.708 --> 00:46:18.344
I heard

00:46:18.344 --> 00:46:21.380
you helped us through all of this,

00:46:21.380 --> 00:46:23.623
even with getting the petition notarized.

00:46:23.623 --> 00:46:25.175
I know you must have been busy,

00:46:25.175 --> 00:46:26.635
so I really can't thank you enough.

00:46:26.635 --> 00:46:28.261
Because of you, we got Woo Joo back,

00:46:28.261 --> 00:46:29.805
I was appointed as his guardian,

00:46:29.805 --> 00:46:31.264
and everything turned out well.

00:46:31.264 --> 00:46:33.767
I'm relieved to hear it all worked out.

00:46:33.767 --> 00:46:35.477
And honestly, it was no big deal.

00:46:35.477 --> 00:46:37.270
I know a lawyer friend of mine,

00:46:37.270 --> 00:46:39.989
and I finally had a chance
to make that connection useful.

00:46:40.830 --> 00:46:42.609
Oh, come on.

00:46:42.609 --> 00:46:44.486
Thank you so much.

00:46:44.486 --> 00:46:46.697
I had been wanting to thank you earlier,

00:46:46.697 --> 00:46:49.491
but I couldn't catch you these last few days.

00:46:49.491 --> 00:46:51.747
I'm getting transferred to the U.S. branch.

00:46:51.747 --> 00:46:54.538
The U.S. branch?

00:46:54.538 --> 00:46:56.540
So now I really am going to be your senior,

00:46:56.540 --> 00:46:58.667
not your manager.

00:46:58.667 --> 00:47:01.089
So when do you leave?

00:47:01.089 --> 00:47:02.233
Two weeks from now.

00:47:02.233 --> 00:47:04.006
That fast?

00:47:04.006 --> 00:47:05.382
Yeah.

00:47:05.382 --> 00:47:08.135
The overseas expo project
has the timeline pretty tight.

00:47:08.135 --> 00:47:10.139
At least I should still be able to give Woo Joo

00:47:10.139 --> 00:47:11.972
his birthday gift before I leave.

00:47:11.972 --> 00:47:14.315
Woo Joo's birthday is next week, right?

00:47:14.975 --> 00:47:16.651
Yeah.

00:47:18.520 --> 00:47:20.700
What?

00:47:20.700 --> 00:47:21.825
[Woo Joo's birthday]
No way.

00:47:21.825 --> 00:47:22.840
It's next week?

00:47:22.840 --> 00:47:23.984
Yeah.

00:47:23.984 --> 00:47:25.705
I knew his birthday was getting close,

00:47:25.705 --> 00:47:27.949
so I was thinking I should start preparing,

00:47:27.949 --> 00:47:30.365
but I had no idea it was already next week.

00:47:30.365 --> 00:47:31.867
Everything has been so hectic lately,

00:47:31.867 --> 00:47:34.122
I didn't even realize time was flying by.

00:47:34.122 --> 00:47:36.580
So what should we start with first?
Where are we supposed to have it?

00:47:36.580 --> 00:47:38.205
What kind of question is that?
At home, obviously.

00:47:38.205 --> 00:47:39.499
Come on, that won't do.

00:47:39.499 --> 00:47:40.747
This is the first birthday

00:47:40.747 --> 00:47:44.106
after I became Woo Joo's uncle
and after you officially became his guardian.

00:47:44.106 --> 00:47:46.289
Come on, it's not like we're throwing
his first birthday party.

00:47:46.289 --> 00:47:48.581
Booking an entire venue would be too much.

00:47:48.581 --> 00:47:51.928
And I bet any place for next week
is already booked solid.

00:47:51.928 --> 00:47:53.914
You think so?

00:47:53.914 --> 00:47:55.872
Then what should we do about the food?

00:47:55.872 --> 00:47:57.122
If people are coming over,

00:47:57.122 --> 00:47:59.360
we're going to need plenty of food.

00:48:00.562 --> 00:48:02.154
What's wrong?

00:48:03.023 --> 00:48:05.408
No, it's nothing.

00:48:08.247 --> 00:48:09.821
Does he understand everything?

00:48:09.821 --> 00:48:11.414
Yeah.

00:48:12.908 --> 00:48:14.581
I'll check on that myself.

00:48:14.581 --> 00:48:15.925
Really?

00:48:15.925 --> 00:48:16.870
How are you going to manage that?

00:48:16.870 --> 00:48:19.498
There's a studio I go to a lot
when I do snap shoots,

00:48:19.498 --> 00:48:21.833
and I think they also rent the place out
for events once in a while.

00:48:21.833 --> 00:48:24.336
My friend. No, President Kim.

00:48:24.336 --> 00:48:26.705
Come on, eat some more ham.

00:48:26.705 --> 00:48:28.340
You're the only one I can count on.

00:48:28.340 --> 00:48:30.955
What's with you all of a sudden?

00:48:30.955 --> 00:48:33.053
People don't usually
make a second birthday party

00:48:33.053 --> 00:48:35.347
- this big, do they?
- That's what I'm saying.

00:48:35.347 --> 00:48:36.737
I tried to tell him he was going too far,

00:48:36.737 --> 00:48:39.184
- but he wouldn't hear it.
- No.

00:48:39.184 --> 00:48:42.414
It's the first birthday party
I get to put together for him.

00:48:42.414 --> 00:48:43.705
So I'm going all out

00:48:43.705 --> 00:48:45.414
and making it as big as possible.

00:48:45.414 --> 00:48:47.164
So fancy that anybody would envy it.

00:48:47.164 --> 00:48:48.819
Nice and extravagant, okay?

00:48:48.819 --> 00:48:51.855
I'm giving him the "whole nine yards."

00:48:51.855 --> 00:48:52.864
Okay.

00:48:52.864 --> 00:48:54.616
Then let me handle the photos.

00:48:54.616 --> 00:48:56.535
You know first birthday party photos
are my thing, right?

00:48:56.535 --> 00:48:57.830
Of course.

00:48:57.830 --> 00:48:59.579
Then I'll be the host.

00:48:59.579 --> 00:49:00.959
I'm good at working a crowd too.

00:49:00.959 --> 00:49:02.082
Love that.

00:49:02.082 --> 00:49:03.169
- Let's do it.
- Okay.

00:49:03.169 --> 00:49:04.788
I knew it.

00:49:04.788 --> 00:49:06.378
That's right up my alley.

00:49:06.378 --> 00:49:09.923
Do you know how much work party food takes?

00:49:09.923 --> 00:49:11.133
You can't do all that alone.

00:49:11.133 --> 00:49:12.634
I really appreciate it, but...

00:49:12.634 --> 00:49:16.205
we were actually just going to book
a catering service.

00:49:16.205 --> 00:49:19.788
A birthday table is mostly
about the effort you put into it.

00:49:19.788 --> 00:49:22.273
And Woo Joo isn't some other kid to me.

00:49:22.273 --> 00:49:25.331
He's practically my own grandchild.

00:49:25.331 --> 00:49:26.398
Well, that's true.

00:49:26.398 --> 00:49:28.358
Plus, Ae Ja's food

00:49:28.358 --> 00:49:30.318
is a whole lot better than anything catered.

00:49:30.318 --> 00:49:33.120
I've been taken care of by Ae Ja's cooking
plenty of times too.

00:49:34.648 --> 00:49:37.409
Then I'll make Woo Joo's cake.

00:49:37.409 --> 00:49:39.372
It's been a while,
so I should show off my skills.

00:49:39.372 --> 00:49:40.914
I'll make it a nice two-tier cake,
just like this.

00:49:40.914 --> 00:49:43.289
What are you suddenly showing off for?

00:49:43.289 --> 00:49:46.209
Mom and I are wearing matching outfits.

00:49:46.209 --> 00:49:48.122
They're having Woo Joo's second birthday party.

00:49:48.122 --> 00:49:49.713
And they're going all out with it.

00:49:49.713 --> 00:49:51.561
What? For a second birthday?

00:49:51.561 --> 00:49:53.456
- Huge?
- Are we having a huge party?

00:49:53.456 --> 00:49:55.604
I'll do the song for the celebration.

00:49:55.604 --> 00:49:58.497
You might not know this,
but I once dreamed of becoming an idol trainee.

00:49:58.497 --> 00:50:00.331
I was the one aiming
to be a trot singer, actually.

00:50:00.331 --> 00:50:01.099
You're doing it with me.

00:50:01.099 --> 00:50:04.102
- Let's do it together.
- Yeah, having a song would be nice.

00:50:04.102 --> 00:50:06.862
- What genre are you?
- Hip-hop.

00:50:07.456 --> 00:50:09.191
Those rice cakes you brought before

00:50:09.191 --> 00:50:10.233
were seriously delicious.

00:50:10.233 --> 00:50:13.577
So I came by to place an order this time.

00:50:22.247 --> 00:50:24.706
Isn't this too big?
How did you even rent this?

00:50:24.706 --> 00:50:26.632
I pulled some strings.

00:50:28.011 --> 00:50:29.788
Tae Hyung.

00:50:29.788 --> 00:50:31.247
What?

00:50:31.247 --> 00:50:32.872
What is all this stuff?

00:50:32.872 --> 00:50:34.747
I've got some special connections.

00:50:34.747 --> 00:50:37.039
Perfect.

00:50:37.039 --> 00:50:40.414
Woo Joo's crazy about animals,
so let them stand out as much as possible.

00:50:40.414 --> 00:50:42.623
Okay, everyone heard that, right?

00:50:42.623 --> 00:50:44.142
Let's get everything in place.

00:50:44.142 --> 00:50:45.692
You heard that, right? Okay.

00:50:51.871 --> 00:50:53.539
What are you doing right now?

00:50:53.539 --> 00:50:54.955
That is not how you do it.

00:50:54.955 --> 00:50:55.990
Come on, get up.

00:50:55.990 --> 00:50:58.664
Okay, move your hips.

00:51:00.164 --> 00:51:02.043
A little more, more.

00:51:03.247 --> 00:51:05.580
Keep going, more.

00:51:05.580 --> 00:51:08.039
Oh my gosh, that's loud.

00:51:08.039 --> 00:51:10.167
Try some of this Sikhye.

00:51:10.835 --> 00:51:12.205
Stop messing with it,

00:51:12.205 --> 00:51:15.163
or you'll break it apart.

00:51:15.163 --> 00:51:16.675
Those are frying up nice and pretty.

00:51:16.675 --> 00:51:19.080
Pretty people make pretty pancakes.

00:51:19.080 --> 00:51:21.039
- And because you're handsome.
- Come on.

00:51:21.039 --> 00:51:23.348
Hey, at least sing it right.

00:51:23.348 --> 00:51:25.497
Are you singing or doing a prayer chant?

00:51:25.497 --> 00:51:27.039
There's no way I can sing with him.

00:51:27.039 --> 00:51:28.331
Forget the song, I'm out.

00:51:28.331 --> 00:51:32.254
Ta-da, the cake's finished.

00:51:34.039 --> 00:51:36.069
Hyun Jin, want to write on the cake yourself?

00:51:36.069 --> 00:51:37.320
Yeah, I'd like that.

00:51:37.320 --> 00:51:38.755
I want to do it too.

00:51:38.755 --> 00:51:39.914
- What do you mean, lettering?
- Lettery?

00:51:39.914 --> 00:51:41.372
Lettering.

00:51:41.372 --> 00:51:44.119
It's when you pipe words onto the cake
and make it look all fancy and artistic.

00:51:44.119 --> 00:51:46.162
All right, let's try this lettering thing.

00:51:46.162 --> 00:51:49.011
- All right, lettering.
- Lettering.

00:51:49.011 --> 00:51:50.664
Write something that says congratulations.

00:51:50.664 --> 00:51:52.426
- Like congratulations?
- Yes.

00:51:53.169 --> 00:51:55.226
Oh no, you ruined it.

00:51:55.226 --> 00:51:56.289
No.

00:51:56.289 --> 00:51:57.955
- She messed it up.
- Oh, that looks good.

00:51:57.955 --> 00:52:00.023
- What do I do?
- It's fine.

00:52:00.023 --> 00:52:04.480
- It's okay.
- It's okay.

00:52:06.814 --> 00:52:08.939
- Woo Joo, let's put your clothes on.
- No.

00:52:08.939 --> 00:52:10.020
- You don't want to?
- Yeah.

00:52:10.020 --> 00:52:12.321
You have to get changed.

00:52:14.441 --> 00:52:15.483
Sun Woo Joo.

00:52:15.483 --> 00:52:17.122
- No.
- You don't want to?

00:52:17.122 --> 00:52:18.236
Pink.

00:52:18.236 --> 00:52:20.539
For now, just go with what Woo Joo wants.

00:52:20.539 --> 00:52:22.490
He's the main character today.

00:52:22.490 --> 00:52:23.491
You think so?

00:52:23.491 --> 00:52:24.914
Come on, let's get dressed.

00:52:24.914 --> 00:52:26.036
Okay.

00:52:26.036 --> 00:52:27.662
I'm going to change too.

00:52:27.662 --> 00:52:29.255
Okay?

00:52:48.475 --> 00:52:50.727
Did you really put all this together
by yourself?

00:52:50.727 --> 00:52:51.773
Yeah.

00:52:51.773 --> 00:52:53.205
No.

00:52:53.205 --> 00:52:55.289
He had me doing all the work.

00:52:55.289 --> 00:52:56.414
Hello.

00:52:56.414 --> 00:52:57.794
Hello.

00:52:57.794 --> 00:52:59.989
I think this is our first time
meeting in person like this.

00:52:59.989 --> 00:53:02.113
I'm Kim Ui Jun.

00:53:02.113 --> 00:53:05.997
He's the photographer friend I told you about.

00:53:05.997 --> 00:53:07.830
I've heard a lot about you.

00:53:07.830 --> 00:53:09.913
Same here. I've heard plenty about you too.

00:53:09.913 --> 00:53:11.118
Hyun Jin.

00:53:14.872 --> 00:53:16.002
You've been through a lot.

00:53:16.002 --> 00:53:17.712
- You're here.
- You've been through a lot.

00:53:17.712 --> 00:53:19.798
I cannot believe Woo Joo's already two.

00:53:19.798 --> 00:53:21.062
I'm seriously about to tear up myself...

00:53:21.062 --> 00:53:22.623
Woo Joo.

00:53:22.623 --> 00:53:24.273
When did you grow up this much?

00:53:24.273 --> 00:53:25.845
Oh, you guys are here.

00:53:25.845 --> 00:53:28.515
Hey, Tae Hyung.

00:53:28.515 --> 00:53:29.830
Congratulations.

00:53:29.830 --> 00:53:31.509
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

00:53:31.509 --> 00:53:32.519
Thank you.

00:53:32.519 --> 00:53:34.403
Where's the little one?

00:53:42.512 --> 00:53:44.955
Happy birthday, baby.

00:53:47.997 --> 00:53:49.883
Take it with both hands.

00:53:51.371 --> 00:53:53.664
It's his second birthday,
and you bought a gold ring too?

00:53:53.664 --> 00:53:56.167
You know how crazy
gold prices are right now, right?

00:53:56.167 --> 00:53:58.636
You are not allowed to change jobs for a while.

00:54:00.273 --> 00:54:02.135
- Woo Joo.
- Woo Joo.

00:54:02.135 --> 00:54:04.308
No running, kids.

00:54:08.497 --> 00:54:10.779
- Ae Ja, you look so pretty.
- Oh, you're here?

00:54:10.779 --> 00:54:12.122
- Congratulations.
- Oh, look at you.

00:54:12.122 --> 00:54:12.872
You two need to get married right now.

00:54:12.872 --> 00:54:14.164
Oh my, Mr. Doo Sik.

00:54:14.164 --> 00:54:17.205
You finally look
like a proper researcher again.

00:54:17.205 --> 00:54:18.231
A researcher?

00:54:18.231 --> 00:54:21.025
His sabbatical is over,

00:54:21.025 --> 00:54:22.694
so he's finally heading back to work.

00:54:22.694 --> 00:54:24.362
Doo Sik.

00:54:24.362 --> 00:54:26.239
Weren't you jobless?

00:54:26.239 --> 00:54:28.867
Hey, from now on

00:54:28.867 --> 00:54:30.368
you call me Director.

00:54:30.368 --> 00:54:32.412
Director.

00:54:32.412 --> 00:54:34.080
Stop smoking.

00:54:34.080 --> 00:54:35.623
That's right, stop smoking.

00:54:35.623 --> 00:54:38.289
You make sure you remember
exactly how much money we gave as gift money.

00:54:38.289 --> 00:54:41.512
Hurry up and pay back
that million won for the boiler.

00:54:46.205 --> 00:54:48.497
- You're here.
- Yeah.

00:54:48.497 --> 00:54:51.026
I wanted to make a good impression
on Woo Joo too.

00:54:51.026 --> 00:54:53.649
Woo Joo, do you like that?

00:54:56.080 --> 00:54:58.153
Yoon Seong.

00:54:59.480 --> 00:55:01.907
Planning Team 3 came together.

00:55:03.331 --> 00:55:04.611
Welcome.

00:55:04.611 --> 00:55:05.778
I know everyone must be busy,

00:55:05.778 --> 00:55:08.872
- so thank you for taking the time to be here.
- All right.

00:55:08.872 --> 00:55:10.414
We're about to start

00:55:10.414 --> 00:55:12.577
Sun Woo Joo's second birthday celebration.

00:55:12.577 --> 00:55:16.164
Everyone, please go ahead and have a seat.

00:55:16.164 --> 00:55:18.583
[Our Universe]

00:55:18.583 --> 00:55:21.753
Before we get started
with Woo Joo's second birthday party,

00:55:21.753 --> 00:55:23.630
let's first hear a few words

00:55:23.630 --> 00:55:26.015
from Woo Joo's uncle.

00:55:34.349 --> 00:55:37.943
I thought Woo Joo belonged only to us,

00:55:39.229 --> 00:55:40.980
but Woo Joo belongs to everyone.

00:55:40.980 --> 00:55:44.067
Every heart in this room came together,
and because of that,

00:55:44.067 --> 00:55:46.778
we, who were so clumsy at all of this,

00:55:46.778 --> 00:55:48.830
ended up becoming a family.

00:55:48.830 --> 00:55:51.824
To Hyun Jin, who stood by me, trusted me,

00:55:51.824 --> 00:55:54.080
and helped me the whole way,

00:55:54.080 --> 00:55:56.037
thank you so much,

00:55:56.037 --> 00:55:58.998
and let's keep doing our best together.

00:55:58.998 --> 00:56:01.884
Thank you, everyone, for being here.

00:56:04.757 --> 00:56:05.846
That was so sweet.

00:56:05.846 --> 00:56:07.556
Me too?

00:56:08.716 --> 00:56:10.843
Today, Woo Joo

00:56:10.843 --> 00:56:12.637
looks like the brightest one here

00:56:12.637 --> 00:56:15.184
because everyone's here together.

00:56:17.183 --> 00:56:19.689
Really,

00:56:19.689 --> 00:56:21.456
thank you so much.

00:56:21.456 --> 00:56:24.691
Then should we all
sing "Happy Birthday" to Woo Joo together?

00:56:24.691 --> 00:56:26.205
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

00:56:26.205 --> 00:56:28.778
Okay, one, two, three.

00:56:28.778 --> 00:56:32.156
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:56:32.156 --> 00:56:35.080
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:56:35.080 --> 00:56:39.546
♪ Happy birthday, dear Woo Joo... ♪
♪ Happy birthday, dear Woo Joo... ♪

00:56:58.770 --> 00:57:01.110
Hyun Joo.

00:58:35.544 --> 00:58:36.577
What?

00:58:36.577 --> 00:58:37.615
Wait, no way.

00:58:37.615 --> 00:58:39.078
Is she pregnant?

00:58:39.078 --> 00:58:40.792
Choo!

00:58:46.247 --> 00:58:48.459
This looks good. Look this way.

00:58:48.459 --> 00:58:50.201
Okay, eyes over here.

00:58:50.201 --> 00:58:51.539
Woo Joo.

00:58:51.539 --> 00:58:53.514
Okay, I'm taking the picture now.

00:58:54.966 --> 00:58:59.838
[African proverb,
it takes a village to raise a child]

00:59:25.788 --> 00:59:29.546
Our universe.

00:59:35.456 --> 00:59:37.080
Blow your nose. Go, blow!

00:59:37.080 --> 00:59:39.017
What do you want?

01:00:30.603 --> 01:00:34.205
Thank you for loving

01:00:34.205 --> 01:00:37.743
Our Universe all this time.